verses.text_plain: He, that being often reproved hardeneth his neck, shall suddenly be destroyed, and that without remedy.
verses.verse_html:
1He, that being often reproved hardeneth his neck, shall suddenly be destroyed, and that without remedy. ▼
▼ He…: Heb. A man of reproofs

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He…: Heb. A man of reproofs
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He…: Heb. A man of reproofs

verses.text_plain: When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice: but when the wicked beareth rule, the people mourn.
verses.verse_html:
2When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice: but when the wicked beareth rule, the people mourn. ▼
▼ in…: or, increased

verses.text_plain: Whoso loveth wisdom rejoiceth his father: but he that keepeth company with harlots spendeth his substance.
verses.verse_html: 3Whoso loveth wisdom rejoiceth his father: but he that keepeth company with harlots spendeth his substance.

verses.text_plain: The king by judgment establisheth the land: but he that receiveth gifts overthroweth it.
verses.verse_html:
4The king by judgment establisheth the land: but he that receiveth gifts overthroweth it. ▼
▼ he…: Heb. a man of oblations

footnotes.body_text: ▼ he…: Heb. a man of oblations
footnotes.body_html: ▼ he…: Heb. a man of oblations

verses.text_plain: A man that flattereth his neighbour spreadeth a net for his feet.
verses.verse_html: 5A man that flattereth his neighbour spreadeth a net for his feet.

verses.text_plain: In the transgression of an evil man there is a snare: but the righteous doth sing and rejoice.
verses.verse_html: 6In the transgression of an evil man there is a snare: but the righteous doth sing and rejoice.

verses.text_plain: The righteous considereth the cause of the poor: but the wicked regardeth not to know it.
verses.verse_html: 7The righteous considereth the cause of the poor: but the wicked regardeth not to know it.

verses.text_plain: Scornful men bring a city into a snare: but wise men turn away wrath.
verses.verse_html:
8Scornful men bring a city into a snare: but wise men turn away wrath. ▼
▼ bring…: or, set a city on fire

footnotes.body_text: ▼ bring…: or, set a city on fire
footnotes.body_html: ▼ bring…: or, set a city on fire

verses.text_plain: If a wise man contendeth with a foolish man, whether he rage or laugh, there is no rest.
verses.verse_html: 9If a wise man contendeth with a foolish man, whether he rage or laugh, there is no rest.

verses.text_plain: The bloodthirsty hate the upright: but the just seek his soul.
verses.verse_html:
10The bloodthirsty hate the upright: but the just seek his soul. ▼
▼ The bloodthirsty: Heb. Men of blood

footnotes.body_text: ▼ The bloodthirsty: Heb. Men of blood
footnotes.body_html: ▼ The bloodthirsty: Heb. Men of blood

verses.text_plain: A fool uttereth all his mind: but a wise man keepeth it in till afterwards.
verses.verse_html: 11A fool uttereth all his mind: but a wise man keepeth it in till afterwards.

verses.text_plain: If a ruler hearken to lies, all his servants are wicked.
verses.verse_html: 12If a ruler hearken to lies, all his servants are wicked.

verses.text_plain: The poor and the deceitful man meet together: the Lord lighteneth both their eyes.
verses.verse_html:
13The poor and the deceitful man meet together: the Lord lighteneth both their eyes. ▼
▼ the deceitful…: or, the usurer

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the deceitful…: or, the usurer

verses.text_plain: The king that faithfully judgeth the poor, his throne shall be established for ever.
verses.verse_html: 14The king that faithfully judgeth the poor, his throne shall be established for ever.

verses.text_plain: The rod and reproof give wisdom: but a child left to himself bringeth his mother to shame.
verses.verse_html: 15The rod and reproof give wisdom: but a child left to himself bringeth his mother to shame.

verses.text_plain: When the wicked are multiplied, transgression increaseth: but the righteous shall see their fall.
verses.verse_html: 16When the wicked are multiplied, transgression increaseth: but the righteous shall see their fall.

verses.text_plain: Correct thy son, and he shall give thee rest; yea, he shall give delight unto thy soul.
verses.verse_html: 17Correct thy son, and he shall give thee rest; yea, he shall give delight unto thy soul.

tokens.text: and he shall give thee rest

verses.text_plain: Where there is no vision, the people perish: but he that keepeth the law, happy is he.
verses.verse_html:
18Where there is no vision, the people perish: but he that keepeth the law, happy is he. ▼
▼ perish: or, is made naked

footnotes.body_html: ▼ perish: or, is made naked

verses.text_plain: A servant will not be corrected by words: for though he understand he will not answer.
verses.verse_html: 19A servant will not be corrected by words: for though he understand he will not answer.

verses.text_plain: Seest thou a man that is hasty in his words? there is more hope of a fool than of him.
verses.verse_html:
20Seest thou a man that is hasty in his words? there is more hope of a fool than of him. ▼
▼ words: or, matters?

verses.text_plain: He that delicately bringeth up his servant from a child shall have him become his son at the length.
verses.verse_html: 21He that delicately bringeth up his servant from a child shall have him become his son at the length.

verses.text_plain: An angry man stirreth up strife, and a furious man aboundeth in transgression.
verses.verse_html: 22An angry man stirreth up strife, and a furious man aboundeth in transgression.

verses.text_plain: A man’s pride shall bring him low: but honour shall uphold the humble in spirit.
verses.verse_html: 23A man’s pride shall bring him low: but honour shall uphold the humble in spirit.

verses.text_plain: Whoso is partner with a thief hateth his own soul: he heareth cursing, and bewrayeth it not.
verses.verse_html: 24Whoso is partner with a thief hateth his own soul: he heareth cursing, and bewrayeth it not.

verses.text_plain: The fear of man bringeth a snare: but whoso putteth his trust in the Lord shall be safe.
verses.verse_html:
25The fear of man bringeth a snare: but whoso putteth his trust in the Lord shall be safe. ▼
▼ safe: Heb. set on high

footnotes.body_html: ▼ safe: Heb. set on high

verses.text_plain: Many seek the ruler’s favour; but every man’s judgment cometh from the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
26Many seek the ruler’s favour; but every man’s judgment cometh from the Lord. ▼
▼ the ruler’s…: Heb. the face of a ruler

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the ruler’s…: Heb. the face of a ruler
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the ruler’s…: Heb. the face of a ruler

verses.text_plain: An unjust man is an abomination to the just: and he that is upright in the way is abomination to the wicked.
verses.verse_html: 27An unjust man is an abomination to the just: and he that is upright in the way is abomination to the wicked.
